          \ parameter is not provided.\n"
        explode: false
        in: query
        name: filterFields
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
        style: form

          \ e.g: [\"LT\", \"GTEQ\", \"CT\"]\nin respective order of values in filterFields\
          \ query parameter.\n\nThe available field filter operations are :\n\nFor\
          \ CHAR type fields:\n\n\"CT\" : contains\n\n\"SW\" : starts-with\n\n\"EW\"\
          \ : ends-with \n\n\"EQ\" : equals\n\nFor NUMERIC type fields:\n\n\"GT\"\
          \ : greater than\n\n\"GTEQ\" : greater than or equals\n\n\"LT\" : lesser\
          \ than\n\n\"LTEQ\" : lesser than or equals\n\n\"EQ\" : equals\n\nNote:\n\
          \nThe request will respond with 400 \n1. If operations other than the above\
          \ mentioned are provided.\n2. If numeric operations are given to char type\
          \ fields instead of char operations.\n3. If char operations are given to\
          \ numeric type fields instead of numeric operations.\n4. If filterFields\
          \ or filterValues query parameters are missing\n   when filterOps is present.\n\
          5. If number of values given for filterOps, \n    filterFields, filterValues\
          \ are different\n6. If exactly one of symbol or date query parameter is\
          \ not provided.\n"

        in: query
        name: filterOps
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
        style: form
      - description: "Can specify the field filter values of the field filter operations\
